# debug_overlay.tas — F3-style info panel regression.
#
# Purpose: confirm the F3-style debug info panel actually paints to the
# top-left when Cmd+D ("debug mode") is on, by comparing the top-left
# corner of two PPM dumps:
#   * baseline: --debug=off + this TAS  → no debug overlay, no panel
#   * panel   : --debug=on  + this TAS  → keyboard HUD + chunk borders
#                                          + F3 panel
#
# Same TAS, same camera state. The keyboard HUD lives in the bottom half
# of the screen and chunk borders are 3D world geometry, so neither
# affects the top-left 320×320 region we sample. The panel rect alone
# (translucent black at alpha 0.5) gives ~5–6 brightness delta per channel.
#
# We can't toggle Cmd+D from a TAS — the parser doesn't support modifier
# keys, so the .D event would arrive without the .super/.ctrl bit set
# and the in-game handler would ignore it. The CLI flag is the way.
#
# Usage (from utils/swindowzig):
#   zig build native -Dexample=voxel
#   ./examples/voxel/tests/debug_overlay.sh
#
# Tick numbering is relative to the first post-loading tick.

# --- Capture mouse so subsequent looks register. ---
1 mouse_down left
2 mouse_up left

# --- Hold the camera still for a few ticks so the FPS sampler settles. ---
4 mouse_move 0 0
8 mouse_move 0 0
12 mouse_move 0 0
20 mouse_move 0 0
30 mouse_move 0 0
